<HEADLINE>
DPRK makes morale-escalating posters for farming
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PYONGYANG, Dec. 12 (Xinhua)
</P>
<P>
The Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) has released
news posters calling on people to make preparations for new
year's farming, the official KCNA news said on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The pictorial posters, presenting the scene of people farming
with enthusiasm, were made by the country's professional art
group.
</P>
<P>
It said the morale-boosting posters would bring rich harvest to
the country.
</P>
<P>
The DPRK has been in shortage of food in recent years due to
natural disasters and other reasons. The country is making
efforts to solve the "food problem."
</P>
